text: Zakerana parambikulamana (common names: Parambikulam frog, Parambikulam wart frog) is a species of frog that is endemic to the Western Ghats, India. It is only known from its type locality, "Parambikulam forests", possibly within the Parambikulam Wildlife Sanctuary in Kerala state. ==References== parambikulamana Category:Frogs of India Category:Endemic fauna of the Western Ghats Category:Taxa named by C. R. Narayan Rao Category:Amphibians described in 1937
